    "causal_summary": "Git workflow orchestrator owning all git/version-control intent: numbered feature worktrees (wt/{NNNN}-{name} branches under .worktrees/), branch creation, conventional commits, pull requests, merge, rebase, finish/integrate, worktree restructure, and cross-platform GitLens/GitKraken MCP workflows (GitHub/GitLab/Azure DevOps/Bitbucket/Jira). It matters because it standardizes how changes move from isolated workspace setup through clean commits to integration and PR completion, and it does not own spec folders / memory (system-spec-kit) or code implementation / tests (sk-code).",
